Mouths were no doubt watering when the world's biggest hot dog was unveiled on Friday at the Miami-Dade County Fair.

Juicy's Outlaw Grill cooked the 125.5 pound dog for three hours on a 100-foot mobile grill, The Miami Herald reports.

By itself, the dog weighed 51 pounds. The other 74.5 pounds come from a bun and a large amount of condiments.

