Brett Enright, founder and CEO of Juicy's Outright Grill, already holds the Guinness World Record for the the largest commercially available hamburger. It costs weighs 777 pounds, costs $5,000, and can be prepared in two days' notice.

The massive hot dog is also available for purchase -- and costs a mere $1,000 in comparison, according to the paper.

Enright, it reports, covered the hot dog in pounds of condiments and sliced onions before it was finally weighed.

Enright and the grill's employees seem to look on proudly at the giant hot dog and its accompanying bun

