Witnesses, including former NFL wide receiver Ike Hilliard, reviewed the weigh-in. A notary prepared documents for Guinness to review, the paper reports.

The giant hot dog was later cut up into samples going for $1 each. Proceeds went to the Miami Rescue Mission.

